    "baseball_pulse": "MY TEAM\nThere is no relevant news for the Weekend Warriors roster today.\n\nMY PROSPECTS\nNo prospect news today.\n\nAROUND THE LEAGUE\nBrandon Woodruff was removed from his start after a velocity dip, a concerning sign for the Brewers pitcher that warrants monitoring. Luis Robert Jr. was placed on the injured list by the Mets, creating a significant outfield vacancy in New York. The Reds placed Brandon Williamson on the injured list while the Mets designated Carl Edwards Jr. for assignment as they continue roster shuffling. Several closers saw action with mixed results: Kyle Finnegan earned a save for Detroit, Gus Varland picked up a save for Washington, and Jack Perkins notched his third save for Kansas City, while Ryan Walker blew a save for San Francisco and appears to be falling out of the closer committee.\n\nBASEBALL TODAY\nThe Philadelphia Phillies completed a historic sweep of the San Francisco Giants in a doubleheader, becoming the first team since 2004 to win both games via walk-off finish. The Phillies' offense exploded with Kyle Schwarber and Trea Turner going back-to-back in Game 2, while Nick Kurtz extended his remarkable streak to 19 consecutive games with a walk, tying Ted Williams' 1941 mark. Yordan Alvarez, Aaron Judge, and Munetaka Murakami are tied atop the home run leaderboard with 12 dingers each as April concludes.",
